The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Sept. 21: The Reserve Bank has amended rules governing non-banking financial companies (NBFC), which mandate these lenders to take into account outstanding liabilities of borrowers while calculating the risk of advancing loans to them. The apex bank said the amendment was necessary in the public interest.

 New Delhi, Sept. 21: The Reserve Bank has kept the inflation rate target at 5-5.5 per cent despite falling oil prices. We stick to our projected estimate of 5 per cent to 5.5 per cent target for inflation, and 7.5 per cent to 8 per cent growth, as stated in the monetary policy, RBI governor Y.V. Reddy said.

 New Delhi, Sept. 21: The company law board today reserved its order on the validity of a petition by minority shareholders of Birla Corporation seeking changes in their original application challenging the share structure of the flagship the MP Birla group firm.

 Mumbai, Sept. 21: Bombay High Court today ruled that it has the jurisdiction to hear the case of Jet Airways and Air Sahara.

 New Delhi, Sept. 21: Guernsey Airtel Limited, a subsidiary of Bharti Global, has won comprehensive licences to offer mobile services in Guernsey, an Island in the English Channel in Europe.




